Product description

SHBC Insulin Double Pen Case

SHBC products

We strive to provide thoughtfully designed products with the intention of making our customers lives easier. We understand that convenience and affordability is key without surrendering quality. Take a look at our collection of diverse products, I believe you will be impressed with our products.

For Insulin Pen Storage

SHBC insulin dual pen case is an ultimate solution to your dual pen storage needs. Refrigerated with PCM (Phase Change Material) ice brick, which is widely used for cold chain distribution of vaccines, blood, insulin, etc., Compared to traditional insulin cases, the innovative case has better cold storage capacity. Just freeze the ice brick for 10 hours and you can bring your required medicine for 8~10 hours without power.

  • Mesh Pocket with Extra Room
  • Damping that Fixes Insulin Pen
  • Thoughtful Webbing Design

A nice gift for diabetic or any people in need

Efficient Cold Storage

Filled with polymer, the cold storage capacity of PCM ice brick is many times that of other materials with the same volume, such as gel ice pack. It can release a balanced amount of cold, even for every detail. PCM is able to control the temperature, which solves the problem of insulin invalidation caused by freezing.

Good Insulation Performance

As a widely-used insulation material, aluminum foil does well. Along with the airtight shell and waterproof zipper, it can effectively cool supplies for 8-10h. Moreover, a hard shell can provide supplies inside with good protection. But inevitably, the zipper may be difficult to pull. Don't worry, it's not a quality problem.

TSA-approved Product

We've given our users the freedom to enjoy a full journey - it's okay to take your medications on board, simply notify the TSA officers that you have medically necessary medications and place them in a separate bin for screening. For details, contact the TSA 72 hours before your departure.

Capacity Statement

The ice brick can keep two insulin pens, don't bother to replace the refill when you run out of the original one. If you are taking two types of insulin, it couldn't be more fitting. The high-capacity mesh bag can hold injection needles, pen refills, alcohol pads and cotton swabs, ensuring a clean and sanitary injection in all respects.

Preparation

Before use gel ice bricks should be placed in the refrigerator for at least 6-10 hours, the gel ice bricks will keep your insulin at a temperature between 2 to 8C for up to 6-8 hours, and under 25C for up to 12-16 hours. (Note: insulin packs should be protected from sunlight)

Check and confirm

Ensure the insulin pen is not expired and check the validity period.

Tips:

The insulin insulation bag helps maintain the temperature stability of your insulin when you're on the go.Try to avoid exposure to extreme temperatures, such as high heat or freezing conditions

Placing insulin

Carefully place the insulin pen and ice pack in the insulated bag, avoiding collision and compression.

Notes for Safe Storage:

1.when not in use, store the ice packs in cool, dry and airproof.

2.to avoid puncturing ice packs, keep sharp appliances away from them.

Using the Case

Close the zipper or fastener of the insulation bag to ensure a tight seal.

Cleaning & Drying:

NOTE:

Do not clean the surface with stiff tools, such as brushes. It may make it hairy or scratched.
